<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="trap-vt">trap <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /træp/    美 /træp/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>设陷阱捕捉；夹住；卡住：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s cruel to trap birds. 
捕鸟是残忍的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I trapped my coat in the car door. 
我的外衣被车门夹住了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>把...困住；使陷入困境：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Having <strong>been trapped in</strong> traffic, he was late for work.
因为交通堵塞，他上班迟到了。</p><footer>译林⑦ – 4</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>留存；储存 (气 / 水等)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Because of the greenhouse effect the Earth is warmed by gases trapped in the atmosphere. 
由于温室效应，储存在大气层中的气体使地球变暖。</p><footer>北师大⑧ – 22</footer></div></div>